window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Wyoming game warden Joe Pickett faces two different kinds of raging beasts—one animal, one human—in this riveting new novel from #1 <i>New York</i> Times bestseller C. J. Box.</p> <p>A rogue grizzly bear has gone on a rampage—killing, among others, the potential fiancé of Joe’s daughter.</p> <p>At the same time, Dallas Cates, whom Joe helped lock up years ago, is released from prison with a special list tattooed on his skin. He wants revenge on the people who sent him away: the six people he blames for the deaths of his entire family and the loss of his reputation and property.</p> <p>Using the grizzly attacks as cover, Cates sets out to methodically check off his list.</p> <p>The problem is, both Nate Romanowski and Joe Pickett are on it.</p>"; 
